Anyway, I'm still looking for that.


</font>
<p>
Just as an aside, I do not consider myself an alcoholic or addicts &#8212; 
if I drink 5 drinks a week, it's a big drinking week for me &#8212; but I
do have loved ones who are alcoholics, and I used to work in a 12
step-based treatment center, where I took clients to innumerable AA/
NA meetings. At one time, before I knew much about AA or had attended
any meetings, I bought into the argument that AA was &quot;the only thing
that works&quot; and thought of AA as a good program. I went to my first
AA meeting eager to discover how wonderful this program was. Boy, was
